BBC 2 HD 22nd Nov 2014
4:55pm to 7:30pm Live

John Inverdale presents live coverage as Wales look to end their losing run against world champions New Zealand at the Millennium Stadium. It is almost 61 years since Wales beat the All Blacks, who arrive in Cardiff defending a 25-match winning run against the Welsh. The last time the teams met was in 2012 when New Zealand claimed a comfortable victory, racing into a 33-0 lead before Wales salvaged some pride as the match ended 33-10. Match commentary by Eddie Butler, Brian Moore and Martyn Williams, with Jonathan Davies, Jeremy Guscott and All Black World Cup winner Ali Williams in the studio.
